### DOD-G corpus
# Raster sources stay local (licensing: self-generated / own photos).
# Only compiled specimens + the report get committed.
test-corpus/raster/
# Sweep artifacts (~26 MB) are regenerable byte-for-byte via trace_scene.py
# (deterministic); kept on disk, out of git. The locked cp8/ld32 cell lives at
# the top level (a1-pines-s42.*), committed. Sweep TABLE is in the report/docs.
test-corpus/traces/sweep/
test-corpus/compiled/sweep/
# Personal-photo-derived specimens (A4/A5) stay local — their compiled SVGs render
# as recognizable people. Only their audit NUMBERS go in the report, never the art.
# EXCEPTION: a4-photo-02 is the DOD-G hero demo asset (owner-approved public,
# 2026-07-06); its trace + compiled graduate. Raw photo source stays local (raster/).
test-corpus/traces/a4-photo-*
!test-corpus/traces/a4-photo-02.*
test-corpus/traces/a5-photo-*
test-corpus/compiled/a4-photo-*
!test-corpus/compiled/a4-photo-02.*
test-corpus/compiled/a5-photo-*
# local-only walk that includes the photo specimens (committed story-gen.json omits them)
test-corpus/story-gen.photos.json

scripts/node_modules/
